  "texts": [
    "For this reason, the Max-Pooling method presented in Eq.",
    "( 25) was used to subsample the feature map in the study.",
    "At this stage, 1 9 2 size Max-Pooling was used to obtain 1-dimensional data.",
    "As a result of the Max-Pooling process, the size of the feature vector of size n 9 1, consisting of a single line, decreases from n 9 1 to (n/2) 9 1.f x ð Þ ¼ max 0; x ð Þð25Þf x ð Þ ¼ min 0; x ð Þð26Þf x ð Þ ¼ mean 0; x ð Þð27ÞApart from these, Min-Pooling and Mean-Pooling methods used in the literature and presented in Eqs.",
    "( 26) and ( 27) were also used."
